1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,800
What if I told you that tiny bacteria are the unsung heroes of our planet's food supply?

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:11,600
Nitrogen fixation bacteria convert atmospheric nitrogen into a form usable by plants.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,000
But how do they do it?

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,200
They live in symbiosis with plants, especially legumes.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:20,400
But not all nitrogen-fixing bacteria are the same!

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,800
Some like Rhizobium form nodules on roots, while others, like Azotobacter, float freely in the soil!

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:31,200
Understanding these bacteria is crucial as they affect agriculture and ecosystems.

8
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,800
Yet, many mysteries remain.

9
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,200
Want to dive deeper into science?

10
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,400
Hit that follow button for more fascinating discoveries!
